comment.author: 77345821@N06
comment._content: This is NOT a Bristol F2b, but rather a French Breguet 14 B2 bomber of the U.S. 96th Aero Squadron. Look at how boxy and slab sided the nose section is, and the "rhino horn" exhaust stack... this is much different than the more slender rounded nose cross section of the Bristol F2b and the Rolls-Royce engine installation w/ the long exhuast stacks that run alongside the fuselage.
